Mix the @Pancake Batter{1%pouch} and @Chocolate Chips{100%g} with the @Ground Cinnamon{1%sachet} in an appropriately-sized #bowl{}.

> Reserve a few chocolate chips to create Christmas designs before serving.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a knob of @Butter{to taste}.

Once hot, add 2 tbsp of batter to the pan until bubbles start to appear, then
turn and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Repeat the process with two-thirds of the batter.

Use the rest of the pancake mix to make smaller pancakes with 1 tbsp batter each.

Plate up larger pancakes with smaller pancakes arranged above to resemble
snowmen.

Use reserved chocolate chips to make the eyes, buttons and scarf.

Design the snowman arms using @Maple Syrup{15%g}, then drizzle the remainder
over the top.